---
title: Orzo and Chorizo Casserole with Burst Tomatoes, Mozzarella, and Spinach
description: This “casserole” requires no baking at all to become gooey and delicious. It’s flavored with woodsy thyme and smoky chorizo for intense depth of flavor in just 30 minutes. Wilting spinach into pasta is one of our favorite tricks for sneaking leafy greens into dinner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/uk-cheesy-tomato-orzo-risotto-8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/orzo-and-chorizo-casserole-8b4567.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/uk-cheesy-tomato-orzo-risotto-571f9ea2f8b25e21418b4567
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 764 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1178 mg
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}(diced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%oz}(halved). Strip the @thyme{1/4%oz}(chopped) of the sprigs and roughly chop the leaves. Remove the @fresh pork chorizo{6%oz} from its casing. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water (at least @water{3%cups}) to a boil.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss the tomatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Place in the #oven{} for about ~{10%minutes}.

Add the thyme, chorizo, and @tomato paste{1%tablespoon} to the pan with the onions. Cook, breaking up the chorizo into pieces, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until the chorizo browns.

Add the @orzo pasta{6%oz} to the pan and toss to coat. Add 2 ½ cups of the salted water and the @veggie stock concentrate{1} to the pan. Reduce to a low simmer and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}, until the orzo is almost al dente. Season with salt and pepper.

> If the water absorbs before the orzo is tender, add another splash of water.

When the orzo is tender, stir in the @mozzarella cheese{2%oz}(shredded), burst tomatoes, and @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Place the @spinach{5%oz} on top and cover for ~{2-3%minutes} to steam. Stir to combine and season generously with salt and pepper, to taste. Serve straight out of the pan and enjoy!